This finiteness property is typically established in the corresponding integral estimate file `SpherePacking.MagicFunction.a.IntegralEstimates.I6`, which is imported. Following the naming conventions of the library (where `Φ₆` corresponds to `I₆`), the lemma establishing the finite integral is `I₆_hasFiniteIntegral`, which takes the hypothesis `hr`.

```lean
theorem Φ₆_integrableOn {r : ℝ} (hr : r ≥ 0) : IntegrableOn (Φ₆ r)
    (Ici (1 : ℝ)) volume := by
  refine ⟨ContinuousOn.aestronglyMeasurable Φ₆_contDiffOn.continuousOn measurableSet_Ici, ?_⟩
  exact I₆_hasFiniteIntegral hr
